                            <comment id="17018724" author="eolivelli" created="Sat, 18 Jan 2020 22:39:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should step away from Jackson.&lt;br/&gt;
Btw it is the very most used library, so maybe in the mid term we could see it come back again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the short term doing it will save us a few cycles for this kind of issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17021279" author="phunt" created="Wed, 22 Jan 2020 16:56:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eolivelli&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eolivelli&quot;&gt;eolivelli&lt;/a&gt; sounds reasonable, can you create a separate jira for that activity?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the mean time I&apos;ve submitted a PR to move to the latest databind version available (2.9.10.2) at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17021924" author="nkalmar" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2020 10:20:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I closed this jira, the upgrade is on master, 3.6 and 3.5 branches, this should fix the CVE for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
